I need to identify the specific line item and value of financing costs incurred by the enterprise to raise funds needed for production and operation.

Looking at the income statement, "Financial Expenses" typically represent the financing costs that a company incurs when borrowing money or raising capital for its operations. These costs include interest payments on loans, bank charges, and other costs related to financing activities.

In the given income statement, I can see the "Financial Expenses" line item with a value of 142115.24 dated 2024-01-28.

Therefore, the value of financing costs incurred by the enterprise is 142115.24.

{"solution": {'value': '142115.24'}}
